The course is 100% web-based (in the Moodle). First, the students are introduced to a comprehensive understanding of collaborative learning through a framework of collaborative problem solving skills. Next, students complete a group assignment related to a collaborative problem solving activity. Once completed, they individually analyse the results from other groups, which are subsequently discussed in a webinar. Next, teaching of collaborative learning is introduced using instructional design principles found in cooperative learning. Then the second group assignment is posted in which students work together to prepare a presentation that will teach their classmates in the other groups about a topic provided by the instructor. Students work on this second assignment in steps with weekly deadlines. A final webinar is held to discuss the presentations from each group. Finally, the course finishes with an examination in the form of an e-test.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce a comprehensive understanding of collaborative learning through a framework of collaborative problem solving skills and to introduce principles for successfully teaching collaborative learning.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing this course, students will be able to: (1) identify and understand different elements of collaborative learning; (2) identify instructional principles for teaching collaborative learning; (3) analyse and assess collaborative learning activities; (4) critically think about methods for assessing collaboration skills.
